International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 29 Jul 2002
From: ProMED-Port@promedmail.org.
Source: Grandeminas.globo online, Wed 24 Jul 2002
<http://grandeminas.globo.com>
Via: Marilda Kersul de Brito Milagres milagres@fclnet.com.br
[Translated by JW][edited]

Brazil: Second Case Confirmed in Minas Gerais
---------------------------------------------
A second case of hantavirus infection has been confirmed in Sao Joao Batista
do Gloria, in the southwest of the state of Minas Gerais. The victim was a
farm administrator aged 34, who died at the beginning of the month [July
2002]. He has been discharged from hospital and is in good health.
A third [suspected] case in the same city is under investigation.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Information on the identity of the viruses, and their specific rodent
hosts, responsible for these recent cases of hantavirus pulmonary syndrome
in Minas Gerais would be appreciated. - Mod.CP]
